  "summary": "Following the disappearance of the \"Morning Star\" diamond, Mr. Bunce and Mr. Bohns attempt to search Yvonne (also referred to as Eve or Ivy) for the gem. Mrs. Maloway and Mrs. Rathbone conduct a thorough search of Yvonne behind a screen, but they find nothing. During the search, Evan Llewellyn opens a window to purchase a newspaper from a newsboy passing below. The men also search the room, including a round table and the chairs where Yvonne had been sitting, but the diamond remains missing.\n\nYvonne eventually reveals her plan: she had previously used rubber cement to replace a fake diamond on her handbag clasp with the real one. She intended to hide the real stone in the empty slot on her bag, but when she attempted to retrieve it from her small black evening clutch, she discovered the diamond was gone. Despite a secondary search of the room, the diamond cannot be found. Suspecting a thief is among the group, Sir George proposes that everyone be searched. The eight individuals undergo searches, yet the diamond remains missing.\n\nIn a subsequent scene, Evan Llewellyn meets with Mr. Parker Pyne to discuss the incident. Evan explains that because Mr. Bunce had locked the door to keep servants out, the diamond must have been taken by someone in the room. Evan expresses concern that his action of buying a newspaper might make it appear as though he threw the diamond to a co-conspirator outside, but Mr. Pyne suggests there may be other ways the gem left the room.",
